      • setupLaunchIntent

        public static android.content.Intent setupLaunchIntent(android.content.Context context,
                                       android.os.Bundle payload)
        Override this method to custom-create the Intent that will be launched when the notification is clicked. Most of the time, calling ETPush.setNotificationAction(String) and ETPush.setNotificationActionUri(android.net.Uri), ETPush.setNotificationRecipientClass(Class), ETPush.setCloudPageRecipient(Class), or ETPush.setOpenDirectRecipient(Class) is sufficient.
        Parameters:
        context - application context
        payload - the data received in the notification
        Returns:
        Intent

      • setupNotificationBuilder

        public static android.support.v4.app.NotificationCompat.Builder setupNotificationBuilder(android.content.Context context,
                                                                         android.os.Bundle payload)
        Override this method if you want complete control over the notification that gets displayed. Return null from your Overridden method to not display any notification for a specific message.
        Parameters:
        context - application context
        payload - data received from the notification
        Returns:
        NotificationCompat.Builder
